At least 23 people died and over hundred were injured in Sikkim after the powerful earthquake left a trail of devastation in the Himalayan state , making relief work difficult due to landslides and road blockages , officials said . Another eight people , who were travelling in a bus of Teesta Urja Limited Company in north district , are presumed to be dead after their vehicle got stuck under the debris , Major General S L Narasimhan of GOC 17 Mountain Division , told reporters here . Deploying 2500 troops and 84 columns , the Army has launched ‘ Operation Madad ’ in the state , he said .“ Around 44 columns are working in Sikkim , another 15 in the east district of state .